<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
     xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
     xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
     xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
     xml:lang="en"
     tal:define="
       utool nocall:context/portal_url;
       charset python:context.portal_registry.get('email_charset', 'utf-8');
       dummy python:request.RESPONSE.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/html;;charset=%s' % charset);
     "
     tal:omit-tag=""
     i18n:domain="plone"
><div tal:omit-tag=""
       i18n:translate="sendto_mailtemplate_body"
  >
This link is sent to you from
    <span tal:replace="structure utool"
          tal:omit-tag=""
          i18n:name="portal_url"
    ></span>

You are receiving this mail because someone read a page at
    <span tal:replace="structure utool/Title"
          tal:omit-tag=""
          i18n:name="portal_title"
    ></span>
and thought it might interest you.

It is sent by
    <span tal:replace="structure options/send_from_address"
          tal:omit-tag=""
          i18n:name="from_address"
    ></span>
     with the following comment:
"<span tal:replace="structure options/comment | nothing"
          tal:omit-tag=""
          i18n:name="comment"
    ></span>"

    <span tal:replace="structure options/title | context/Title"
          tal:omit-tag=""
          i18n:name="document_title"
    ></span>

    <span tal:replace="structure options/description | context/Description"
          tal:omit-tag=""
          i18n:name="document_description"
    ></span>

    <span tal:replace="structure options/url | context/absolute_url"
          tal:omit-tag=""
          i18n:name="document_url"
    ></span>
  </div>
--
  <span tal:replace="structure options/email_from_name"></span>

</div>
